headline: Copart shares tumble as quarterly results miss expectations
summary: Investing.com -- Copart Inc (NASDAQ:CPRT) saw its shares slide 11.1% in after-hours trading Thursday following the release of its second-quarter fiscal results. The online vehicle auction leader reported earnings and revenue that fell short of Wall Street estimates for the period ended January 31, 2026. The company posted quarterly earnings per share of $0.36, missing the $0.39 consensus set by analysts. This figure represents a 10.0% decline from the $0.40 per share reported in the same quarter
